title: Gabby's Dollhouse
description: This colorful series leads preschoolers room to room through a fantastical dollhouse of delightful mini-worlds and irresistible kitty characters.

title: Spy Kids 4: All the Time in the World
description: A retired spy is called back into action, and to bond with her new step-children, she invites them along for the adventure to stop the evil Timekeeper from taking over the world.

title: Mad Monster Party?
description: On the Isle of Evil, the head of the "World Organization of Monsters" reveals his imminent retirement and that he has refined a formula for total destruction, only to be upset when the monsters try to steal the formula and kill his nephew.

title: Trolls 2: World Tour
description: When the Queen of the Hard Rock Trolls tries to take over all the Troll kingdoms, Queen Poppy and her friends try different ways to save all the Trolls.

title: All That Jazz
description: Director/choreographer Bob Fosse tells his own life story as he details the sordid career of Joe Gideon, a womanizing, drug-using dancer.

title: Across the Universe
description: The music of The Beatles and the Vietnam War form the backdrop for the romance between an upper-class American girl and a poor Liverpudlian artist.

title: Campfire Christmas
description: Romance rekindles for Peyton and her closest friends during a holiday themed reunion which Peyton's parents decide to host in their family owned summer camp before selling it.

title: Fantasia
description: A collection of animated interpretations of great works of Western classical music, ranging from the abstract to depictions of mythology and fantasy, and settings including the prehistoric, supernatural and sacred.

title: Smash
description: More drama occurs behind the scenes than on stage, as the team prepares an ambitious Broadway musical on the life of Marilyn Monroe.

title: Wish
description: 17-year-old Asha and her goat Valentino navigate Rosas, the kingdom of wishes, where wishes can literally come true.

title: The Mighty Boosh
description: Surreal British comedy in which Vince Noir and Howard Moon have adventures filled with oddball characters while working as Zoo Keepers, before pursuing a musical career and running a second-hand shop.

title: Tenacious D in the Pick of Destiny
description: To become the greatest band of all time, two slacker, wannabe-rockers set out on a quest to steal a legendary guitar pick that gives its holders incredible guitar skills, from a maximum security Rock and Roll museum.

title: Dreamgirls
description: A trio of black female soul singers cross over to the pop charts in the early 1960s, facing their own personal struggles along the way.

title: Big Time Rush
description: Four hockey players from Minnesota aspire to become a boyband. Kendall, Logan, Carlos, and James embark on a life-changing journey and face challenges along the way.

title: High School Musical 3: Senior Year
description: As seniors in high school, Troy and Gabriella struggle with the idea of being separated from one another as college approaches. Along with the rest of the Wildcats, they stage a spring musical to address their experiences, hopes and fears about their future.

title: Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham...
description: After marrying a poor woman, rich Rahul is disowned by his father and moves to London to build a new life. Years later, his now-grown younger brother Rohan embarks on a mission to bring Rahul back home and reunite the family.

title: The Lure
description: In Warsaw, a pair of mermaid sisters are adopted into a cabaret. While one seeks love with humans the other hungers to dine on the human population of the city.

title: Blue's Clues
description: Blue is a puppy who puts her paw prints on three clues. Steve or Joe has to deduce the clues (with the help of off-screen children) to figure out what Blue wants to do.

title: Hair
description: Claude Bukowski leaves the family ranch in Oklahoma for New York where he is rapidly embraced into the hippie group of youngsters led by Berger, yet he's already been drafted. He soon falls in love with Sheila Franklin, a rich girl but still a rebel inside.

title: South Park: Bigger, Longer & Uncut
description: When Stan Marsh and his friends go see an R-rated movie, they start cursing and their parents think that Canada is to blame.

title: Charlotte's Web
description: Wilbur is a farm pig who's terrified that he'll end up on the dinner table. His friend Charlotte, a charming spider, comes to his rescue. She weaves words into her web, convincing the farmer that Wilbur is too special a pig to kill.

title: Pete's Dragon
description: An orphan boy and his magical dragon come to town with his abusive adoptive parents in pursuit.

title: Zootopia+
description: The adventures of the creatures of the most incredible metropolis: Zootopia.

title: Hoodwinked
description: Little Red Riding Hood, the Wolf, the Woodsman, and Granny all tell the police the events that led up to their encounter.

title: Winnie the Pooh
description: While searching for honey, Pooh and his friends embark on an adventure to find Eeyore's missing tail and rescue Christopher Robin from an unknown monster called The Backson.

title: Funny Girl
description: The life of Fanny Brice, famed comedienne and entertainer of the early 1900s. We see her rise to fame as a Ziegfeld girl, subsequent career, and her personal life, particularly her relationship with Nick Arnstein.

title: Voy a pasármelo bien
description: David and Layla, two teenagers who really like "Hombres G" and they like each other too, but everything he does to win her over ends badly. Thirty years later they meet again and realize that the feelings have not completely disappeared.

title: The Color Purple
description: Musical adaptation of Alice Walker's novel about the life-long struggles of an African American woman living in the south during the early 1900s.

title: Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip
description: The Chipmunks believe that Dave plans to propose to his new girlfriend in Miami.--and dump them. They have three days to get to him and save themselves not only from losing Dave but also from gaining a terrible stepbrother.

title: The Magic Flute
description: 17-year-old Tim Walker as he travels from London to the Austrian Alps to attend the legendary Mozart boarding school. There, he discovers a centuries-old forgotten passageway into the fantastic world of Mozart's "The Magic Flute."

title: Hamster & Gretel
description: Follows Gretel and her pet Hamster after receiving new abilities. Now, protective older brother Kevin must figure out how to work with both Gretel and her pet to protect their city from mysterious dangers.

title: Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara
description: Three friends decide to turn their fantasy vacation into reality after one of their friends gets engaged.

title: Fame
description: A chronicle of the lives of several teenagers who attend a New York high school for students gifted in the performing arts.

title: Paint Your Wagon
description: Two unlikely prospector partners share the same wife in a California gold rush mining town.

title: Bugsy Malone
description: The classic gangster story of Bugsy Malone told with an all-child cast.

title: Blue's Big City Adventure
description: Josh and Blue head to New York City to audition for a big Broadway musical.

title: The Wiz
description: An adaptation of "The Wizard of Oz" that tries to capture the essence of the African-American experience.

title: Blue's Clues & You
description: Each game of Blue's Clues involves problem-solving, viewer interaction, and of course, a stop for "mailtime!" In this reboot, the animated ensemble cast is back with a new host: Josh, who's just learning how to play Blue's Clues.

title: An American Tail
description: While emigrating to the United States, a young Russian mouse gets separated from his family and must relocate them while trying to survive in a new country.

title: Grease Live!
description: After enjoying a summer romance, high school students Danny and Sandy are unexpectedly reunited when she transfers to Rydell High. There Sandy must contend with cynical Rizzo and the Pink Ladies in attempt to win Danny's heart again.

title: Lady and the Tramp
description: The romantic tale of a sheltered uptown Cocker Spaniel dog and a streetwise downtown Mutt.

title: The Producers
description: After putting together another Broadway flop, down-on-his-luck producer Max Bialystock teams up with timid accountant Leo Bloom in a get-rich-quick scheme to put on the world's worst show.

title: The Return of the King
description: Two Hobbits struggle to destroy the Ring in Mount Doom while their friends desperately fight evil Lord Sauron's forces in a final battle.

title: Seven Brides for Seven Brothers
description: In 1850 Oregon, when a backwoodsman brings a wife home to his farm, his six brothers decide that they want to get married too.

title: Pee-wee's Playhouse
description: Pee-Wee Herman and his friends have wacky, imaginative fun in his unique playhouse.

title: The Muppet Movie
description: Kermit and his newfound friends trek across America to find success in Hollywood, but a frog legs merchant is after Kermit.

title: Teen Beach Movie
description: Two surfing lovers, whose doomed relationship is nearing to a close, find themselves swept into a dimension-traversing wave that sends them into a beach movie musical in the 60's.

title: Hedwig and the Angry Inch
description: A gender-queer punk-rock singer from East Berlin tours the U.S. with her band as she tells her life story and follows the former lover/band-mate who stole her songs.

title: Nine
description: Famous film director Guido Contini struggles to find harmony in his professional and personal lives, as he engages in dramatic relationships with his wife, his mistress, his muse, his agent, and his mother.

title: The Little Mermaid II: Return to the Sea
description: To protect her from a sea witch, Ariel's daughter is not allowed in the ocean; but when she becomes 12, she runs away to an adventure under the sea.

title: Jesus Christ Superstar
description: Film version of the musical stage play, presenting the last few weeks of Christ's life told in an anachronistic manner.

title: The Sword in the Stone
description: A poor boy named Arthur learns the power of love, kindness, knowledge and bravery with the help of a wizard called Merlin in the path to become one of the most beloved kings in English history.

title: Oliver & Company
description: A lost and alone kitten joins a gang of dogs engaged in petty larceny in New York City.

title: Evita
description: The hit musical based on the life of Eva Perón (Evita Duarte), a B-picture Argentinian actress who eventually became the wife of Argentinian president Juan Domingo Perón, and the most beloved and hated woman in Argentina.

title: Rebelde
description: Six teenagers with different lives and personalities attend a prominent private school with only one thing in common: their vocation and passion for music.

title: My Little Pony: A New Generation
description: After the time of the Mane 6, Sunny--a young Earth Pony--and her new Unicorn friend Izzy explore their world and strive to restore Harmony to Equestria.

title: Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked
description: Playing around while aboard a cruise ship, the Chipmunks and Chipettes accidentally go overboard and end up marooned in a tropical paradise. They discover their new turf is not as deserted as it seems.

title: Rio 2
description: It's a jungle out there for Blu, Jewel, and their three kids after they're hurtled from Rio de Janeiro to the wilds of the Amazon. As Blu tries to fit in, he goes beak-to-beak with the vengeful Nigel and meets his father-in-law.

title: Camelot
description: The story of the marriage of England's King Arthur to Guinevere. The plot of illegitimate Mordred to gain the throne and Guinevere's growing attachment to Sir Lancelot, threaten to topple Arthur and destroy his "round table" of knights.

title: The Hocus Pocus 25th Anniversary Halloween Bash
description: Fans, cast members, and celebrities alike gather at Hollywood Forever Cemetery to commemorate the 25th Anniversary of Disney's Hocus Pocus and its long-lasting impact.

title: Gnomeo & Juliet
description: Separated by a garden fence and a feud, are blue gnomes on one side and red gnomes on the other. This doesn't stop blue Gnomeo and red Juliet from falling in love with each other. Do they have a future together?

title: Teletubbies
description: Four creatures with televisions in their stomachs have fun in their magical world.

title: Star
description: A trio of women form a musical group in Atlanta.

title: Galavant
description: A musical comedy adventure featuring a knight on a quest for love who helps a childish king to see the error of his ways.

title: The King and I
description: A widow accepts a job as a live-in governess to the King of Siam's children.

title: Puppy Dog Pals
description: Fun-loving pug puppies, brothers Bingo and Rolly, have thrill-seeking appetites that take them on exhilarating adventures in their neighborhood and around the globe.

title: Fame
description: The stories of the students and faculty of the New York City High School for the Performing Arts.

title: Music
description: Zu is newly sober when she receives news that she is to become the sole guardian of her half-sister named Music, a young girl on the autism spectrum. The film explores two of Sia's favorite themes: finding your voice and creating family.

title: The Music Man
description: Traveling con artist Harold Hill targets the naïve residents of a small town in 1910s Iowa by posing as a boys' band leader to raise money before he can skip town.

title: Attack of the Killer Tomatoes!
description: A group of scientists band together to save the world from mutated killer tomatoes.

title: Oklahoma!
description: In Oklahoma, several farmers, cowboys and a traveling salesman compete for the romantic favors of various local ladies.

title: My Little Pony: The Movie
description: After a dark force conquers Canterlot, the Mane 6 embark on an unforgettable journey beyond Equestria where they meet new friends and exciting challenges on a quest to use the magic of friendship to save their homeland.

title: Muppets Most Wanted
description: While on a grand world tour, The Muppets find themselves wrapped into an European jewel-heist caper headed by a Kermit the Frog look-alike and his dastardly sidekick.

title: Dumbo
description: Ridiculed because of his enormous ears, a young circus elephant is assisted by a mouse to achieve his full potential.

title: Ladybug & Cat Noir: The Movie
description: Ladybug & Cat Noir Awakening, is an upcoming animated musical film based on Miraculous: Tales of Ladybug & Cat Noir. It will be released in Fall 2021, or Early 2022.

title: Blue Hawaii
description: After arriving back in Hawaii from the Army, Chad Gates (Elvis Presley) defies his parents' wishes for him to work at the family business and instead goes to work as a tour guide at his girlfriend's agency.

title: Don't Hug Me I'm Scared
description: Three puppets known as Red Guy, Yellow Guy and Duck learn about creativity from a talking sketchbook.

title: The Meaning of Life
description: The comedy team takes a look at life in all of its stages in their own uniquely silly way.

title: Guys and Dolls
description: In New York, a gambler is challenged to take a cold female missionary to Havana, but they fall for each other, and the bet has a hidden motive to finance a crap game.

title: The Star Wars Holiday Special
description: Chewbacca and Han Solo try to get to the Wookiee homeworld of Kashyyyk to celebrate Life Day, but are impeded by an Imperial blockade. Chewie's family passes the time with various forms of entertainment.

title: King Creole
description: A troubled youth's singing sets New Orleans rockin'. With a sweet girl to love him and nightclubbers cheering, it seems he will shake off his past and head for the top. But will a mobster and his man-trap moll snare him in a life of crime?

title: Kuch Kuch Hota Hai
description: During their college years, Anjali was in love with her best-friend Rahul, but he had eyes only for Tina. Years later, Rahul and the now-deceased Tina's eight-year-old daughter attempts to reunite her father and Anjali.

title: Romance & Cigarettes
description: This down-and-dirty musical set in the world of working-class New York tells the story of a husband's journey into infidelity and redemption when he must choose between his seductive mistress and his beleaguered wife.

title: Heathers: The Musical
description: Veronica Sawyer does her best to survive her senior year while navigating the beautiful but cruel Heathers, the new to school Jason "J.D." Dean, and the constant pressure to fit in with everyone else.

title: The Swan Princess
description: A power-hungry sorcerer curses a princess to live as a swan by day in this tale of everlasting love.

title: Meet the Feebles
description: Multiple animals and insects experience the sleazier side of show business while working on a variety show.

title: Arthur
description: Based on the books by Marc Brown, these are the adventures of Arthur, an 8-year-old aardvark, and his family and friends as they grow up and learn how to be good neighbors to one another.

title: High School Musical 2
description: School's out for summer and the East High Wildcats are ready to make it the time of their lives after landing jobs in a wealthy country club owned by Sharpay and Ryan's family.

title: How the Grinch Stole Christmas!
description: A grumpy hermit hatches a plan to steal Christmas from the Whos of Whoville.

title: Isn't It Romantic
description: A young woman disenchanted with love mysteriously finds herself trapped inside a romantic comedy.

title: The Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh
description: In this collection of animated shorts based on the stories and characters by A.A. Milne, Winnie the Pooh, a honey-loving teddy bear, embarks on some eccentric adventures.

title: Smallfoot
description: High up on a mountain peak surrounded by clouds, a secret Yeti society lives in peace and harmony. One day, a Yeti witnesses an airplane crash; Inside lies "Smallfoot", a legendary creature that will rock the society to its core.

title: The Garbage Pail Kids Movie
description: Dodger must confront the struggles of life as he is visited by the Garbage Pail Kids and intimidated by some older bullies.

title: Home on the Range
description: To save their farm, the resident animals go bounty hunting for a notorious outlaw.

title: The Brave Little Toaster
description: A group of dated appliances embark on a journey to the city to find their master after being abandoned in a cabin in the woods.

title: The Sound of Music Live!
description: A live telecast of the famous Rodgers and Hammerstein musical.

title: Everyone Says I Love You
description: A New York girl sets her father up with a beautiful woman in a troubled marriage while her stepsister gets engaged.

title: Camp Rock
description: At a music camp for gifted teens, a popular teen idol overhears a girl singing and sets out to find who the talented voice belongs to. What he doesn't know is that the girl is actually a camp kitchen worker with a fear of being heard.

title: Bubble Guppies
description: The adventures of six fish-tailed kids- Molly, Gil, Oona, Deema, Nonny, and Goby.

title: The Great Mouse Detective
description: Basil, the rodent Sherlock Holmes, investigates the kidnapping of a toy maker and uncovers its link to his archenemy, Professor Ratigan.

title: Tiana
description: Tiana continues to explore New Orleans in a musical series.

title: Thumbelina
description: This retelling of the Hans Christian Andersen classic fairy tale has the digit-sized heroine evading the clutches of various toads, moles, and beetles before she can proceed with her courtship with her dream lover, Prince Cornelius.

title: Santa Claus Is Comin' to Town
description: A mailman reveals the origin of Santa Claus.

title: High Society
description: With socialite Tracy Lord about to remarry, her ex-husband - with the help of a sympathetic reporter - has 48 hours to convince her that she really still loves him.

title: Cinderella
description: Although mistreated by her cruel stepmother and stepsisters, Cinderella is able to attend the royal ball through the help of a fairy godmother.

title: The New Adventures of Pippi Longstocking
description: After her father's ship is carried off by a sudden storm, the spunky Pippi Longstocking is stranded with her horse, Alfonso, and monkey, Mr. Nilsson, and takes up residence in the old family home, which is thought by neighborhood children to be haunted. Soon, two children, Tommy and Annika, venture into the house only to meet up with Pippi. The three soon become frien...

title: Hello, Dolly!
description: Matchmaker Dolly Levi travels to Yonkers to find a partner for "half-a-millionaire" Horace Vandergelder, convincing his niece, his niece's intended, and his two clerks to travel to New York City along the way.

title: Lemonade Mouth
description: Five high school kids, Olivia, Wendall, Stella, Charlie, and Mo, meet in detention and start a band based on the lemonade vending machine outside the detention room.

title: Eli Stone
description: San Francisco lawyer Eli Stone begins to see things, which leads him to discover a brain aneurysm. But his visions lead him to accept cases with little monetary gain but a lot of moral goodness.

title: Rapunzel's Tangled Adventure
description: Set between Walt Disney Animation Studios' "Tangled" and its short film "Tangled Ever After," this animated adventure/comedy series unfolds as Rapunzel acquaints herself with her parents, her kingdom and the people of Corona.

title: Barbie as The Princess and the Pauper
description: Inspired by Mark Twain's fascinating novel, Princess Anneliese finds an unexpected friendship when she meets her humble look-alike, Erika. Will the Princess and the Pauper thwart the plans of the Queen's scheming advisor, Preminger?

title: Spellbound
description: Spellbound tells the story of Elian, a teenager who comes of age using her magical powers to defend her family when the opposing forces of light and darkness threaten to divide her kingdom.

title: Carmen
description: A modern-day reimagining of one of the classical opera 'Carmen'.

title: Kal Ho Naa Ho
description: Naina, an introverted, perpetually depressed girl's life changes when she meets Aman. But Aman has a secret of his own which changes their lives forever. Embroiled in all this is Rohit, Naina's best friend who conceals his love for her.

title: Gigi
description: Weary of the conventions of Parisian society, a rich playboy and a youthful courtesan-in-training enjoy a platonic friendship which may not stay platonic for long.

title: Scrooge: A Christmas Carol
description: A supernatural, time-travelling, musical adaptation of Charles Dickens's cult Christmas story

title: Lagaan: Once Upon a Time in India
description: The people of a small village in Victorian India stake their future on a game of cricket against their ruthless British rulers.

title: Elena of Avalor
description: Princess Elena has saved her magical kingdom, Avalor, from an evil sorceress and must learn to rule as its crown princess. Elena's adventures will lead her to understand that her new role requires thoughtfulness, resilience and compassion.

title: Funny Face
description: An impromptu fashion shoot at a book store brings about a new fashion model discovery in the shop clerk.

title: Blue Story
description: A gang war dooms the lifelong bond of south London friends in this acclaimed crime drama that features its writer-director as a rapping Greek chorus.

title: Muppet Treasure Island
description: The Muppets' twist on the classic tale.

title: Dirty Dancing
description: A musical re-imagining of the 1987 film, Dirty Dancing (1987).

title: Over the Moon
description: In this animated musical, a girl builds a rocket ship and blasts off, hoping to meet a mythical moon goddess.

title: Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani
description: Kabir and Naina bond during a trekking trip. Before Naina can express herself, Kabir leaves India to pursue his career. They meet again years later, but he still cherishes his dreams more than bonds.

title: A Hard Day's Night
description: Over two "typical" days in the life of The Beatles, the boys struggle to keep themselves and Sir Paul McCartney's mischievous grandfather in check while preparing for a live TV performance.
